  "time_ut": 1661576024,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0d9a \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0daf\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab \u0dc4\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dab\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hati Peradeniya University says that the food cost of a family has increased",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A special study of the University of Peradeniya found that the monthly consumption expenditure (the amount spent on various items including food) of an average family in Sri Lanka, which used to be Rs. Mr. Wasantha Athukorala, Professor of the Department of Economics and Statistics, told Lankadeepa.",
        "The professor says that the monthly consumption expenditure of an extremely poor family in Sri Lanka, which used to be four thousand five hundred (14,500) rupees in 2019, has increased by eleven thousand (11,000) rupees to twenty five thousand five hundred (25,500) rupees today due to the inflationary situation. He also mentioned that the society includes a population of 21 lakhs.",
        "He also pointed out that due to the inflationary situation, the monthly expenses of a high-income family in Sri Lanka, which used to be one hundred and ninety-eight thousand rupees, have now increased by one hundred and forty thousand rupees to three hundred and forty-five thousand rupees.",
        "Mr. Wasantha Athukorala said that the high income group includes a population of 20 lakhs.",
        "Also, the professor said that it was found in the study that the monthly expenditure of a middle income family in Sri Lanka, which used to be 48 thousand rupees, has increased by 35 thousand rupees to 83 thousand rupees due to the inflationary situation.",
        "Meanwhile, by the last year 2019, there were twenty one lakh people in the country whose monthly consumption expenditure exceeded one lakh rupees and that number has now increased to eighty four lakhs.",
        "He further stated that it appears that the number of people whose monthly consumption expenditure has exceeded one lakh rupees has increased not because of the increase in the standard of living but because of the huge increase in the price of consumer goods."
      ],
